title.title: Buses replace trains between Willesden Junction and Wembley Central

texts: Buses will replace Bakerloo line and Silverlink Metro trains between Willesden Junction and Wembley Central on the morning of Sunday 29 January until 12:20 as emergency track repair works are being carried out by Network Rail in the Stonebridge Park area.
Emergency track repair works are being carried out in the Stonebridge Park area
There will be no Bakerloo line service North of Willesden Junction during that time.
A rail replacement bus service running every 10 minutes will operate on Sunday morning, stopping at Willesden Junction, Harlesden, Stonebridge Park and Wembley Central.
Valid London Underground and National Rail tickets will be accepted on this service.

For 24-hour information on public transport in London, please call: 020 7222 1234.
